<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_Beginner_LiveMode_Emotions" s="314253">
  <T n="name">0xA7D0FF3A<!--String: "Emotions"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_Emotions_1.png" n="image">2f7d0004:00000000:8827ddeca2898c0c</T>
      <T n="text">0xD6E9BE68<!--String: "Sims are feeling creatures! Their current mood, or <b><font color='#199C2C'>Emotion</font></b>, has a big impact on what they do and how they do it. \n\nA <b><font color='#199C2C'>positive Emotion</font></b> may help your Sim to build <b><font color='#199C2C'>Skills</font></b>, develop <b><font color='#199C2C'>Relationships</font></b>, and get promoted in their <b><font color='#199C2C'>Career</font></b>. \n\n<b><font color='#199C2C'>Negative Emotions</font></b>, however, may cause your Sims to <b><font color='#199C2C'>fail</font></b> at things or <b><font color='#199C2C'>stop</font></b> them from doing those things altogether until they feel better.\n"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_Emotions_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:8827ddeca2898c0f</T>
      <T n="text">0x661B7A79<!--String: "A Sim’s <b><font color='#199C2C'>Emotion</font></b> is based on their current <b><font color='#199C2C'>Moodlets</font></b>. \n\nEach Moodlet has a different strength, duration, and associated Emotion. The main <b><font color='#199C2C'>source</font></b> of Moodlets are your Sim’s <b><font color='#199C2C'>Needs</font></b>, <b><font color='#199C2C'>Traits</font></b>, and recent <b><font color='#199C2C'>experiences</font></b>.\n\nYou can see your Sim’s <b><font color='#199C2C'>current Emotion</font></b> and their <b><font color='#199C2C'>Moodlets</font></b> by their <b><font color='#199C2C'>portrait</font></b>. Hover the cursor over the Sim or a Moodlet to learn more!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_Emotions_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:8827ddeca2898c0e</T>
      <T n="text">0xD8F16692<!--String: "Taking care of your Sim’s <b><font color='#199C2C'>Needs</font></b> and participating in activities associated with their <b><font color='#199C2C'>Traits</font></b> (such as reading books if you have the Bookworm Trait) are good ways to get <b><font color='#199C2C'>positive Moodlets</font></b>.\n\nYou can make <b><font color='#199C2C'>negative Moodlets go away</font></b> faster with some <b><font color='#199C2C'>self care</font></b>. Taking a shower, using the mirror for a pep talk or to calm down, or crying in bed may be helpful, depending on what Emotion your Sim is dealing with."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
